<body>

<h1>@HI{{beki}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<p>
<ol>
<li> @Vplain{{}}(non-past) <strong>@HI{{beki}}</strong> @HI{{desu}}
<li> @Anastem{{}}@HI{{dearu}} <strong>@HI{{beki}}</strong>
<li> @N{{}}@HI{{dearu}} <strong>@HI{{beki}}</strong>
</ol>
</p>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{beki}}</strong> is an auxiliary that expresses the speaker's judgement that something should be
in some state.
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{beki}}</strong> expresses the idea that something should be in a certain state because it is their
responisbility or duty or because it is the right thing to do.

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{kono@KJ{{argument^sentence}}ha@KJ{{write}}ki@KJ{{straightaway}}su<strong>beki</strong>da.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    This thesis should be rewritten.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{sonnnakotowo@KJ{{person}}ni@KJ{{say}}u<strong>beki</strong>jaarimasenn.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    You shouldn't say that kind of thing to people.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{@KJ{{mister}}mo@KJ{{come}}ru<strong>beki</strong>deshitayo.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    You should have come too.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{@KJ{{he}}ha@KJ{{tie^marriage}}nankasu<strong>beki</strong>janakattanda.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    He shouldn't have married.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{kono@KJ{{status*quo^attitude}}ga@KJ{{present^reality}}dearu<strong>beki</strong>da.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    This state should be the reality.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{beki}}</strong> can also express the idea that somone is expected to do something.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{suru<strong>beki</strong>@KJ{{place}}ni@KJ{{scribe^mention}}ganai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    There's no description where there should be one.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{beki}}</strong> can immediately precede a noun.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{@KJ{{tale}}su<strong>beki</strong>kotoha@KJ{{whole^section^tale}}shimashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    I told you everything I should tell you.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
Either @HI{{suru<strong>beki</strong>}} or @HI{{su<strong>beki</strong>}} is acceptable.
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{beki}}</strong> should not be used to someone of higher status.
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{beki}}</strong> is similar to @HI{{mono da}} but the latter expresses a social norm (e.g. "Students should study")
and cannot be applied to a specific situation (e.g. "<em>You</em> should study.").
</p>

